-- Tabcorp's World Cup Sales Boosted to More Than $175 Million, Review Says
-- Rebecca Keenan
-- 2010-07-11T21:40:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-11/tabcorp-s-world-cup-sales-boosted-to-more-than-175-million-review-says.html

          
          
             The soccer World Cup increased
Tabcorp Holdings Ltd. sales by 20 percent to A$120 million,
compared with the previous event in Germany four years ago, the
Australian Financial Review reported, citing the company.  
 Australians bet more than A$200 million on the event held
in South Africa, the newspaper said, citing Tabcorp Managing
Director of Sports Betting Craig Nugent. The event also
delivered 20,000 new customers to Tabcorp, it said.  
